.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-FSCK 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 1.0.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-fsck \- validate issue data integrity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue fsck
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validate all issue refs for data integrity.
The following checks are performed on each issue:
.IP \(bu 2
Ref name matches UUID format
.RI ( xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx ).
.IP \(bu 2
All commits in the chain use the empty tree.
.IP \(bu 2
The root commit has required
.B State:
and
.B Format\-Version:
trailers.
.IP \(bu 2
The commit chain has exactly one root commit.
.PP
A summary of checked issues and error count is printed.
The exit status is non-zero if any errors are found.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Only show errors; suppress per-issue "ok" messages.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Check all issues:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue fsck
.fi
.RE
.PP
Quiet mode for scripting:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue fsck --quiet || echo "Issues have errors"
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-fsck (1)
